<div id="content"  class="clearfix">
	<form action="" method="get" id="gridForm" autocomplete="off" class="clearfix">
		<p class="tip on"><span><strong>April 2nd 2013:</strong> Spring cleaning! Arrow key navigation is now less intrusive, .png downloads are now transparent + small improvements.</span><a href="#" class="toggle">Hide tip</a></p>
		<p style="margin: 0.5em 5px;"><small>Grid examples to get you started: <a href="#/960/12/20/10" class="gridLink">960.gs 12 col grid</a>, <a href="#/950/24/10/0" class="gridLink">Blueprint 24 col grid</a>, <a href="#/320/4/10/15" class="gridLink">Custom 4 col iPhone grid</a></small></p>
		<div class="col first">
			<label>Max width: 
				<span class="input"><input type="text" size="4" name="maxWidth" id="input_width" value="960" /> px</span>
			</label>
			<label>Columns:
				<span class="input"><input type="text" size="4" name="columns" id="input_columns" value="4" /> cols</span>
			</label>
		</div>
		<div class="col">
			<label>Gutter width: 
				<span class="input"><input type="text" size="4" name="gutter" id="input_gutter" value="20" /> px</span>
			</label>
			<label>Margin width: 
				<span class="input"><input type="text" size="4" name="margin" id="input_margin" value="20" /> px</span>
			</label>
		</div>
		<div id="results" class="col"></div>
	</form>

	<div id="result"></div>

	
	
	<form id="download" action="download.php" method="post">
		<h3>Download grid for</h3>
		<input type="hidden" name="pageWidth" id="download_page" />
		<input type="hidden" name="columns" id="download_columns" />
		<input type="hidden" name="colWidth" id="download_colwidth" />
		<input type="hidden" name="gutter" id="download_gutter" />
		<input type="hidden" name="margin" id="download_margin" />
		
		<input type="submit" class="downloadButton" name="type" value="Adobe Illustrator" title="A standard Illustrator .ai file with pre-made guides on a separate layer" />
		<input type="submit" class="downloadButton" name="type" value="Adobe Photoshop" title="A .jsx script that uses magic (no, really) to place the guides for you. Just double click and start designing!" />
		<input type="submit" class="downloadButton" name="type" value="Other (png image)" title="A grid image. Place it on a separate layer and reduce the opacity for the best effect." />
